Key Match Events: Shakib Al Hasan starred with a half-century in Bangladesh's win over Netherlands.
Bangladesh posted 159/5 with Shakib Al Hasan scoring an unbeaten 64*.
Bangladesh bowlers restricted the Netherlands to 134/8, winning by 25 runs.
Taskin Ahmed took 2 wickets for 30 runs, including the final wicket of Tim Pringle.
Rishad Hossain finished with leading figures of 3/33 from his four overs.
Mustafizur Rahman delivered economical returns of 1/12 from his four overs.
Tanzid Hasan scored 35 from 26 balls in a partnership with Shakib Al Hasan.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Sybrand Engelbrecht took a stunning catch for Netherlands against Bangladesh.
A bouncer got stuck in Tanzid Hasan's helmet during the match.
